    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a bit scary to hear. It sounds like there could be some really sneaky or hidden risks buried in there that I might not notice right away. Are there any specific words or phrases in that paragraph that act as \"red flags\" for these kinds of hidden liabilities?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A few phrases in that clause are definitely worth scrutinizing, as they are where the real teeth of the liability lie. Look out for \"any and all losses, damages, liabilities, deficiencies, claims, actions, judgments, settlements, interest, awards, penalties, fines, costs, or expenses of whatever kind.\" That string of words is a massive catch-all, meaning they are trying to cover every conceivable type of financial hit. You should be wary of anything that uses language like \"any and all\" because it means they are casting the widest possible net for potential problems.",
      "source": "target",
